The paper presents a general approach to rounding semidefinite programming relaxations obtained by the Sum-of-Squares method, which is a common technique in computational complexity (cs.CC) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also applies this approach to three specific problems: approximating a low degree multivariate polynomial (cs.CG), finding a vector in a subspace (cs.LG), and recovering a planted sparse vector (cs.IT). These sub-categories are ordered based on the frequency of papers related to these topics in each category.
